Captain Ohashi Kazuya requests to transport

9
00:02:10,740 --> 00:02:12,460
a large amount of experimental materials

10
00:02:12,460 --> 00:02:14,370
to 810. It's urgent.

11
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,720
Thank you.

12
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:29,720
It's been deciphered?

13
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:33,930
This is the first time for us to find his trace

14
00:02:33,930 --> 00:02:35,310
in the Japanese army's telegrams

15
00:02:35,310 --> 00:02:36,450
after Ohashi left Shanghai.

16
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:37,720
The telegram was sent from somewhere in the southwest.

17
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,780
But we don't know the exact location.

18
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:43,400
I've never heard of this 810.

19
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,329
Sir,

20
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,380
according to the files

21
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:50,250
of the Cherry Blossom Project brought back by Sundial,

22
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:52,140
I think it's very likely that 810 is the name

23
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:54,100
of a new Japanese biochemical bacteria unit

24
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:56,430
established after Ohashi left Shanghai.

25
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:59,810
It's hard to confirm it

26
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,310
with this telegram alone.

27
00:03:01,690 --> 00:03:02,550
How about this?

28
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:04,340
I'll show it to Wei Qingming.

29
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:05,980
You go ask the Telecom Section

30
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:07,530
to continue to track them.

31
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:08,560
Okay.

32
00:03:13,510 --> 00:03:15,030
Wen Yishan and Qin Moqing

33
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:17,090
have given the files to Wei Qingming.

34
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:18,750
Wei Qingming has also browsed

35
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:21,030
the files related to the Cherry Blossom Project

36
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:22,290
and asked Li Shaotang.

37
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:24,270
Now, they have made

38
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:26,430
capturing Ohashi their highest-priority mission.

39
00:03:26,430 --> 00:03:28,760
Got it. I'll report to Chief immediately.

40
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:30,190
Tanaka.

41
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:37,110
You've been in Chongqing for two years.

42
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,010
How much longer do you want to stay?

43
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,340
You don't want to see me?

44
00:03:42,510 --> 00:03:44,230
You want me to leave so much?

45
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,200
Back then, you told me

46
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:49,360
what you wanted was just a list.

47
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:51,070
Now,

48
00:03:51,740 --> 00:03:52,940
what else do you want?

49
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,450
Don't worry.

50
00:03:56,990 --> 00:03:58,290
I won't

51
00:03:58,650 --> 00:03:59,880
let you

52
00:04:00,090 --> 00:04:01,260
die.

53
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,990
If you do this again,

54
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:09,340
I can kill you anytime.

55
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,010
You won't.

56
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:22,190
We intercepted

57
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,830
two telegrams about Ohashi.

58
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:26,350
One was sent by the new Japanese commander

59
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:28,710
who invaded Hong Kong to Ohashi Kazuya.

60
00:04:28,730 --> 00:04:30,860
He invited him to a celebration.

61
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:32,880
The other is the reply of Ohashi.

62
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:35,590
Ou Xiao'an

63
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,380
was among his retinue.

64
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,680
In other words,

65
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:42,640
the intelligence station in Shanghai was destroyed

66
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,560
because Ou Xiao'an betrayed us.

67
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,990
Captain, when I first joined the NBIS,

68
00:04:50,990 --> 00:04:52,370
I already heard about Ohashi Kazuya

69
00:04:52,370 --> 00:04:53,680
and his Cherry Blossom Project.

70
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,030
It's been a long time,

71
00:04:55,030 --> 00:04:56,620
but we haven't made any progress.

72
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:58,350
Now the project was started suddenly.

73
00:04:58,350 --> 00:05:00,780
Also, we consecutively found three telegrams

74
00:05:00,780 --> 00:05:02,760
related to it within a month.

75
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,560
I'm worried...

76
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:06,780
Qin Moqing, what are you worried about?

77
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:10,670
The Intelligence Department's men

78
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:13,290
risked their lives to get the information.

79
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,090
Who are you to be worried

80
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,780
that the information is fake?

81
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:20,050
I didn't say the information is fake.

82
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:21,650
It's just that it's not normal.

83
00:05:21,650 --> 00:05:23,030
We should confirm if it's true

84
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:23,550
before taking action, right?

85
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:24,710
You still mean

86
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:26,530
the information is fake, right?

87
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,880
Who spoiled you?

88
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:30,920
Wen, she's your student, right?

89
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,580
Shouldn't you say something?

90
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:35,220
Moqing,

91
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,190
even if the information is fake,

92
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:39,800
it won't cause any harm to send a few people to Hong Kong.

93
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,990
If Ohashi doesn't show up,

94
00:05:40,990 --> 00:05:42,600
they'll just have a wasted journey, right?

95
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,560
What if the information is true?

96
00:05:49,860 --> 00:05:50,870
Wei,

97
00:05:51,730 --> 00:05:52,710
I think if Ohashi

98
00:05:52,710 --> 00:05:54,350
appears in Hong Kong,

99
00:05:54,370 --> 00:05:56,050
he should be executed on the spot.

100
00:05:56,050 --> 00:05:56,810
I agree.

101
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,640
I'll send someone there immediately.

102
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:02,490
If you have made up your mind,

103
00:06:02,510 --> 00:06:04,970
I want to go to Hong Kong to carry out the task.

104
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,240
Wen,

105
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,320
this...

106
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,400
Moqing,

107
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,690
go out.

108
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:22,740
She came here not long ago.

109
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:23,690
She doesn't know the rules.

110
00:06:23,690 --> 00:06:26,040
After all, she's the daughter of Qin Jiru.

111
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,440
She's a bit hot-tempered,

112
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:29,060
but she's capable.

113
00:06:29,090 --> 00:06:31,040
I think she's very hot-tempered.

114
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:33,370
Alright.

115
00:06:33,409 --> 00:06:35,210
Wen, train her well.

116
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,290
Don't let her

117
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,300
become like Ou Xiao'an.

118
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:44,730
This time, I'll lead a team

119
00:06:44,790 --> 00:06:45,990
to Hong Kong myself.

120
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:48,700
I can't use the Operations Department's men.

121
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,260
You understand, right?

122
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:52,030
Yes.

123
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:53,930
Here's my advice.

124
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:56,250
If Ou Xiao'an shows up in Hong Kong,

125
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,950
bring him back first.

126
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,140
Execute him

127
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,170
after we interrogate him.

128
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:03,820
It's a prudent suggestion.

129
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:05,410
Bring him back.

130
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:06,390
Okay.

131
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:11,940
[April 1943, Hong Kong]

132
00:07:21,910 --> 00:07:23,910
Meet me downstairs in 15 minutes.

133
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:24,880
-Yes.
-Yes.

