144
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,770
[Hong Kong Republic Hotel]

145
00:09:36,870 --> 00:09:40,050
[Intelligence Officer Ohashi Kazuya of the East China Expeditionary Army was assassinated in Hong Kong]

146
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:46,070
Wei!

147
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:49,970
What did you promise me before you went to Hong Kong?

148
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:51,970
Bring Ou Xiao'an back alive.

149
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:53,410
Wen.

150
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,890
Wen, calm down.

151
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:57,670
I was about

152
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:59,190
to tell you this.

153
00:09:59,210 --> 00:10:02,010
He died in Hong Kong! What's the point of explaining?

154
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:00,720
[Intelligence Officer Ohashi Kazuya of the East China Expeditionary Army was assassinated in Hong Kong]

155
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:03,810
I had to.

156
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,050
Why?

157
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,780
I only brought a few people,

158
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:09,570
but we were facing a company of the Japanese army.

159
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,290
I was lucky that I could

160
00:10:11,330 --> 00:10:12,750
accomplish the mission given by Kuomintang

161
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:14,420
and come back alive.

162
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:16,500
The situation was...

163
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,450
I almost died there.

164
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:24,110
You got hurt?

165
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:25,810
Let me see if it's serious.

166
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:28,660
Stop acting, Wei.

167
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:30,460
I know very well

168
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:31,950
what you are capable of.

169
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:33,180
You did it?

170
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:34,260
I...

171
00:10:34,290 --> 00:10:36,010
It must be her, right?

172
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:37,910
I did it to cover them. Well...

173
00:10:38,350 --> 00:10:39,390
You did it, right?

174
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:41,940
I killed him.

175
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:44,480
[For the Public Good]

176
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:46,810
Wen,

177
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:48,530
I'm also very sorry

178
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:50,170
about what happened to Xiao'an.

179
00:10:50,170 --> 00:10:51,770
But he betrayed Kuomintang.

180
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:53,950
He will die sooner or later.

181
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,830
The higher-ups have been rushing me

182
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:00,530
to submit the report on this mission.

183
00:11:00,530 --> 00:11:02,550
Don't worry. I'll include

184
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:05,010
all your contributions

185
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:05,710
in the report.

186
00:11:05,710 --> 00:11:06,640
No need for that.

187
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,000
I didn't do anything!

188
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:11,860
[For the Public Good]

189
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:11,740
Wen,

190
00:11:11,950 --> 00:11:12,950
my condolences.

191
00:11:18,430 --> 00:11:20,510
Submit this newspaper

192
00:11:18,610 --> 00:11:20,440
[Intelligence Officer Ohashi Kazuya of the East China Expeditionary Army was assassinated in Hong Kong]

193
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:21,460
with the report.

194
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:22,430
Okay.

195
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:23,160
Also,

196
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:26,330
the aged tea brought back from Hong Kong

197
00:11:26,330 --> 00:11:28,000
is a good thing. Put it away now.

198
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,530
I'll make some tea for you someday. It's rare.

199
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:34,980
Your acting skills have improved a lot.

200
00:11:36,710 --> 00:11:41,570
[For the Public Good]

201
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,450
[Serve the people with dedication and sincerity] [Integrity as the foundation, universal love and brotherhood]

202
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:48,320
[March 1945, Chongqing]

203
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:51,500
[Name: Ando Motoyoshi]

204
00:11:56,140 --> 00:11:57,110
Stop!

205
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,540
What are you doing?

206
00:12:02,980 --> 00:12:03,770
Wen,

207
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:05,980
you want to carry out an autopsy

208
00:12:05,980 --> 00:12:07,810
on the prisoner without permission.

209
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:09,510
This is against the rule, right?

210
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,390
Captain Wei,

211
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:12,830
I guess Vice Captain Wen is doing this

212
00:12:12,830 --> 00:12:14,480
because he loves his disciple very much.

213
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,480
I can understand.

214
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:16,910
Who are you to interrupt?

215
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,900
In the Chongqing Station,

216
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:20,340
I can do

217
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,510
whatever I want.

218
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,670
Why are you so angry?

219
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:24,700
Wen,

220
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:27,400
the higher-ups gave us Ando.

221
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,380
If you carry out an autopsy on him

222
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:31,020
without the higher-ups' permission,

223
00:12:31,020 --> 00:12:33,080
what should I tell them if they ask me?

224
00:12:33,530 --> 00:12:34,860
Yes, Vice Captain Wen.

225
00:12:35,010 --> 00:12:36,950
After all, he already died here.

226
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:39,330
If we don't leave his body intact,

227
00:12:39,590 --> 00:12:41,520
we won't be able to explain, right?

228
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:44,390
If we don't find out the cause of Ando's death,

229
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:47,530
do you think the higher-ups will let us go?

230
00:12:47,790 --> 00:12:50,350
His cause of death is very clear now.

231
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,840
Ou Xiao'an killed him.

232
00:12:53,860 --> 00:12:55,550
You were there.

233
00:12:55,930 --> 00:12:57,360
Ou Xiao'an just squeezed his throat for a while.

234
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,710
How could that kill him?

235
00:13:03,310 --> 00:13:04,520
Wei,

236
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:08,900
there must be another reason for Ando's death.

237
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,520
Now his body is here.

238
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:12,940
We have the upper hand.

239
00:13:13,070 --> 00:13:14,710
If the body is transferred

240
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:16,190
and someone plays a trick,

241
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:18,070
we'll suffer

242
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:21,140
if the higher-ups blame us.

243
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:30,440
You.

244
00:13:30,830 --> 00:13:31,860
Where are you from?

245
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:32,990
The Third Hospital.

246
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,510
Give me a conclusion

247
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:36,630
within an hour.

248
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:37,820
Okay.

249
00:13:39,970 --> 00:13:40,640
Continue.

250
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,530
What's the conclusion?

251
00:13:53,050 --> 00:13:54,500
We detected arsenic

252
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:55,510
in Ando Motoyoshi's blood.

253
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:57,160
I think he died of arsenic poisoning.

254
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:59,220
Arsenic poisoning?

255
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,020
Yes.

256
00:14:02,830 --> 00:14:04,430
The onset of acute arsenic poisoning varies

257
00:14:04,430 --> 00:14:05,610
depending on the dose

258
00:14:05,610 --> 00:14:07,320
and gastric filling degree.

259
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:09,000
It could take

260
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,960
five to 30 seconds

261
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:11,620
or 14 to 18 hours.

262
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:12,370
In other words,

263
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:14,100
during the past 18 hours,

264
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:15,750
anyone who had contact with Ando

265
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,610
could be the one who poisoned him.

266
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:18,840
I've written down the details

267
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,480
in the autopsy report.

268
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,430
Poisoned?

269
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:24,240
Mao Renxing,

270
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:25,730
what's wrong with you?

271
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:27,120
This shouldn't have happened, right?

272
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,520
Why are you looking at me?

273
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,090
It has nothing to do with me.

274
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:33,030
Wei,

275
00:14:33,060 --> 00:14:34,550
if Ando

276
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:37,340
was really poisoned,

277
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:40,800
none of us can get away with it.

278
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:49,510
Captain Wei,

279
00:14:50,050 --> 00:14:50,890
I really searched Ou Xiao'an

280
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:52,700
before the interrogation.

281
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,180
I didn't find anything...

282
00:14:55,210 --> 00:14:56,220
Wei.

283
00:14:58,300 --> 00:14:59,160
How about this?

284
00:14:59,530 --> 00:15:00,830
You and Miao

285
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:03,700
